# Cursor IDE Rules for Universal Notebook Project

This file contains project-specific rules. For global development standards, see:
- ~/.cursor/development-rules.md
- ~/.cursor/neatness-standard.md
- ~/.cursor/ai-assistant-rules.md

## Project-Specific Rules

### Code Style
- Follow existing TypeScript/React patterns
- Use Prisma for database operations
- Docker-based execution environment

### Documentation
- Keep troubleshooting in docs/troubleshooting/active/
- Archive resolved issues to docs/troubleshooting/archived/
- Co-locate scripts with related documentation

### Verification
- Always verify code exists before suggesting changes
- Read files before modifying
- Test solutions in Docker environment

